turn.5: Are there any other interesting aspects about this article?
turn.6: They have an HNRNPK homology (KH) domain embedded in a 200-amino acid region called the GSG domain.
turn.7: Who are the other members of the RNA-binding protein family?
turn.8: Other members of this family include SAM68 (KHDRBS1) and SF1 .
turn.9: Who are the newest members of the family?

turn.11: Is there any additional information about Qki?
turn.12: The QKI gene is implicated as being important in schizophrenia, and QKI controls translation of many oligodendrocyte-related genes.
